<TITLE> 1 killed, 3 wounded in Keraniganj 'shootout' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 10 (bdnews24.com)A suspected criminal was killed and three others were wounded on Friday in a 'gunfight' with RAB in Keraniganj on the outskirts of the capital, an official of the elite force said. The dead was named as 'Tapan', 28, while the injured were identified as 'Hridoy', 22, 'Pappu', 18 and Mohammad Kamal, 25. The injured were admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. The gunfight ensued at Khejurbagh as a group of six-to-seven criminals fired at a team of RAB-10 team in plainclothes at night. RAB returned the fire, captain SM Kamal Hossain said. The four were captured from the scene and admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where one of them died from bullet wounds, Hossain added. Two .9 mm pistols and four rounds of bullets were also recovered from them, Hossain said. The four were criminals on the Keraniganj police list, he said and added that Tapan faced more than one charges including murder. RAB had been working for quite sometime in Keraniganj as crime rate recently went up there, he said. Nine people were shot dead and at least 20 others injured in the capital and on its fringes in so-called gunfight with RAB in the last two months. Besides, three died and at least 23 sustained injuries in alleged firefight with the police. bdnew
